<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-04T15:50:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-04T15:50:00-05:00" n="867" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d867">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.82/27: Airgram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Braden</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-04T15:50:00-05:00">February
                                    4, 1944—3:50 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 5—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A–264. Reference Department’s confidential instruction no. 2709 of
                            December 31, 1943. The Cuban Navy Department has given its permission
                            for the installation of aids to navigation at Manzanillo as detailed in
                            the Department’s instruction under reference and has <pb facs="0907" n="893" xml:id="pg_893"/> likewise undertaken to make all the
                            necessary arrangements for the occupation of land sites at the expense
                            of the Cuban Government for the four shore lights. The United States
                            Coast Guard may therefore proceed immediately with the installation at
                            Manzanillo of the proposed aids to navigation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>